review_blob: This is another excellent beer by Terrapin. Very drinkable, one of my first experiences of a rye beer.  Had this in a Hotel Lounge in downtown Atlanta. I wish I could get this in Omaha.

This is a big beer, very hoppy,(DUH!) enjoyable. I found this by accident. I didnt expect to find a big beer like this in Georgia due to their beer laws. I took this to my aunts  house and my cousins who havent discovered beers like this really enjoyed it and it was a welcomed treat in Nebraska too!

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: This is an incredible beer. It is the best of both worlds. The Wheat meets the Hops. This is a beer that would satisfy the hophead and the wheat fanatic.I had this beer in America and at the Schneider brewery In Kelheim, Germany. If you can get this, dont pass it up!!

An excellent example of a classic American lager. Very unassuming, at home while fishing or visiting with friends. Definitely worth the trip to Minnesota to see the Shells brewery and get this beer if not available in your area
A very tasty beer! Very hard to find on tap anywhere, Very common in bottles. A very good example of a German Pilsener. Great color and head retention, and fabulous aroma!
An interesting beer, however, if this was a geuze, I feel it would be undrinkable due to it being too sour.Thanks to Sledge Jr.
